---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const title = "About Jitan Gupta · AI Adoption Practitioner in Mumbai";
const description = "Mumbai-based AI adoption practitioner. I teach engineering teams and non-technical professionals how to use AI in real work, with deep specialization in Claude Code, MCP, and agentic workflows.";
---
<Layout title={title} description={description}>
	<section class="bg-[#F8FAFC] mx-2">
		<div class="bg-white max-w-screen-xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 rounded-b-2xl">

			<!-- The Short Version -->
			<div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center md:space-x-8">
				<img src="/jitan-bg.png" alt="Jitan Gupta" class="h-[280px] md:h-[380px]">
				<div class="mt-6 mb-6 md:mt-0">
					<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Hey, I'm Jitan 👋</h1>
					<p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
						I'm a Mumbai-based AI adoption practitioner. I help engineering teams and non-technical professionals put AI into real daily work, with deep specialization in Claude Code, the Model Context Protocol (MCP), and agentic workflows.
					</p>
					<p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
						Ten years in tech (nine in software, one in platform engineering), twelve years running a general store before that, five startup attempts in between. Teaching is what ties it all together. I publish in Hinglish on YouTube and run hands-on meetups in Mumbai.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="w-full h-[2px] bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-gray-300 to-transparent my-8"></div>

			<!-- The Long Version -->
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Long Version</h2>

				<div class="space-y-8">
					<div>
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">The General Store (12 years before tech)</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							Before I wrote a line of code, I ran a general store for 12 years. That's where I learned operations, customer problems, and the difference between what people say they need and what actually helps them.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">The Engineering Years (2015 to Present)</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							I spent ten years as a .NET developer and then platform engineer. Cloud, Kubernetes, multi-tenant SaaS, identity platforms. The kind of systems where downtime costs real money and shortcuts create production incidents.
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3 text-gray-700">
							That's the lens I bring to AI adoption. Not everything needs AI, and the things that do need it done carefully.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">The Startup Attempts (2018 to 2022)</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							I tried to build five startups in parallel with my engineering career. One scaled a SaaS product to 30K monthly active users before shutting down. The others taught me what most AI hype skips over: distribution, sustainability, and knowing when to stop.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Now: Teaching AI Adoption</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							I build with AI tools daily. Claude Code, Cowork, MCP servers, OpenClaw, open-source models. I publish what works on YouTube in Hinglish 🇮🇳, ship open-source tools, and run hands-on meetups in Mumbai where people build real things with AI.
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3 text-gray-700">
							My deepest specialization is the Claude side: Claude Code workflows, Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers, and agentic setups (Git Worktree, OpenClaw, Cowork). I also teach broadly across Claude, ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini for teams choosing between tools.
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3 text-gray-700 font-medium">
							I don't sell hype. I teach from practice.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Things You Can Verify</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-700">
							Teaching is easy to fake. Shipping is not. Here's the work that backs the channel:
						</p>
						<ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-gray-700 list-disc list-inside">
							<li>
								<a href="https://github.com/jitangupta/cb-mcp-server" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline font-medium">cb-mcp-server</a>: a real MCP server I built live on YouTube, connecting my Content Board PWA to Cowork. Public repo, episode-by-episode build log.
							</li>
							<li>
								<a href="https://github.com/jitangupta/cowork-boilerplate" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline font-medium">Cowork Boilerplate</a>: open-source workflow scaffolding for Claude's desktop agent, shared in the Claude Discord #build-with-claude channel.
							</li>
							<li>
								<a href="https://github.com/jitangupta/content-board" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline font-medium">Content Board</a>: a production PWA managing my entire video pipeline. The thing the MCP server talks to.
							</li>
							<li>
								<a href="https://www.youtube.com/@jitangupta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline font-medium">YouTube channel</a>: weekly long-form Hinglish content on Claude Code, MCP, and agentic workflows.
							</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="w-full h-[2px] bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-gray-300 to-transparent my-8"></div>

			<!-- What I Focus On -->
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What I Focus On</h2>
				<ul class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
					<li class="flex items-start">
						<span class="text-primary-500 mr-3 text-xl font-bold shrink-0">→</span>
						<span><span class="font-semibold">AI-Assisted Development:</span> How engineering teams can use AI tools without losing code quality or architectural control</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start">
						<span class="text-primary-500 mr-3 text-xl font-bold shrink-0">→</span>
						<span><span class="font-semibold">AI for Non-Technical Professionals:</span> Document automation, workflow optimization, and task management using AI. No coding required.</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start">
						<span class="text-primary-500 mr-3 text-xl font-bold shrink-0">→</span>
						<span><span class="font-semibold">Responsible Adoption:</span> When to use AI, when not to, and how to evaluate tools without getting locked into vendor hype</span>
					</li>
				</ul>
			<p class="mt-6 text-gray-700">
				Want to work together? Check out my <a href="/services" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline">services</a>.
			</p>
			</div>

			<div class="w-full h-[2px] bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-gray-300 to-transparent my-8"></div>

			<!-- Connect -->
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-6 text-center">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Let's Connect</h2>
				<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
					Based in Mumbai. Building and teaching globally.
				</p>
				<div class="flex justify-center gap-4 flex-wrap">
					<a href="https://www.youtube.com/@jitangupta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg shadow-md bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 transition text-sm sm:text-base">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M2.5 17a24.12 24.12 0 0 1 0-10 2 2 0 0 1 1.4-1.4 49.56 49.56 0 0 1 16.2 0A2 2 0 0 1 21.5 7a24.12 24.12 0 0 1 0 10 2 2 0 0 1-1.4 1.4 49.55 49.55 0 0 1-16.2 0A2 2 0 0 1 2.5 17"/><path d="m10 15 5-3-5-3z"/></svg>
						Watch on YouTube
					</a>
					<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jitangupta/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 justify-center px-5 py-3 text-base font-medium text-center text-gray-900 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-100 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-gray-100 text-sm sm:text-base">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M16 8a6 6 0 0 1 6 6v7h-4v-7a2 2 0 0 0-2-2 2 2 0 0 0-2 2v7h-4v-7a6 6 0 0 1 6-6z"/><rect width="4" height="12" x="2" y="9"/><circle cx="4" cy="4" r="2"/></svg>
						Connect on LinkedIn
					</a>
					<a href="https://github.com/jitangupta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 justify-center px-5 py-3 text-base font-medium text-center text-gray-900 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-100 focus:ring-4 focus:ring-gray-100 text-sm sm:text-base">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M15 22v-4a4.8 4.8 0 0 0-1-3.5c3 0 6-2 6-5.5.08-1.25-.27-2.48-1-3.5.28-1.15.28-2.35 0-3.5 0 0-1 0-3 1.5-2.64-.5-5.36-.5-8 0C6 2 5 2 5 2c-.3 1.15-.3 2.35 0 3.5A5.403 5.403 0 0 0 4 9c0 3.5 3 5.5 6 5.5-.39.49-.68 1.05-.85 1.65-.17.6-.22 1.23-.15 1.85v4"/><path d="M9 18c-4.51 2-5-2-7-2"/></svg>
						See on GitHub
					</a>
					<a href="https://topmate.io/jitangupta" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg shadow-md bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 transition text-sm sm:text-base">
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="18" height="18" x="3" y="4" rx="2" ry="2"/><line x1="16" x2="16" y1="2" y2="6"/><line x1="8" x2="8" y1="2" y2="6"/><line x1="3" x2="21" y1="10" y2="10"/></svg>
						Book a Call
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>

		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
